==English==
===Etymology===
From Dutch [[steken]] ‘thrust, stick’ + [[snee]], a dialectal variant of [[snijden]] ‘cut’.  The ''st-'' of [[steken]] later assimilated to the ''sn-'' of [[snee]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/snɪk ɔ: sni:/}}

===Verb phrase===
'''snick or snee'''
# ''(intransitive, obsolete)'' to [[cut]] or [[thrust]] while fighting with a [[knife]]; to use a knife as a [[weapon]]

===Related terms===
*[[snickersnee]]

